        <div class="content-main">

          <h2>Understanding Credit Card Eligibility in India</h2>
          <p>Credit card eligibility depends on several factors that banks and financial institutions evaluate to determine your creditworthiness. Understanding these criteria before applying can significantly improve your approval chances and help you avoid unnecessary hard inquiries on your credit report — which can temporarily lower your CIBIL score by 5-10 points per inquiry.</p>
          <p>Different card categories have varying eligibility thresholds. Entry-level and secured cards are accessible to most applicants, while premium cards like HDFC Infinia or Amex Platinum require a high income and excellent credit history. TrueCred's eligibility checker uses a soft inquiry to show you pre-qualified offers without affecting your credit score.</p>

          <h2>Key Eligibility Criteria</h2>
          <ul class="feature-list">
            <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Age Requirement:</strong> Primary cardholder must be 21-60 years (salaried) or 21-65 years (self-employed); add-on cards available from 18 years</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Minimum Income:</strong> ₹15,000/month for entry-level cards, ₹25,000-₹50,000 for mid-tier, and ₹1 lakh+ for super-premium cards</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Credit Score (CIBIL):</strong> 750+ for best approval odds; 700+ for most cards; secured cards available even with scores below 600</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Employment Stability:</strong> Minimum 1 year of total work experience and 6 months with current employer for salaried applicants</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Existing Credit History:</strong> Clean repayment track record with no defaults, write-offs, or settlements in the past 3 years</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Debt-to-Income Ratio:</strong> Total EMIs and credit card dues should not exceed 40-50% of your gross monthly income</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>Eligibility by Card Category</h2>
          <p>Different card types have different thresholds. Here's a quick reference:</p>

          <table class="rate-table">
            <thead>
              <tr>
                <th>Card Category</th>
                <th>Min. Income</th>
                <th>Min. CIBIL Score</th>
                <th>Key Requirement</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>Entry-Level / Basic</strong></td>
                <td>₹15,000/month</td>
                <td>700+</td>
                <td>Stable employment, basic KYC documents</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>Rewards & Cashback</strong></td>
                <td>₹25,000/month</td>
                <td>720+</td>
                <td>Regular spending pattern, clean credit history</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>Travel & Forex</strong></td>
                <td>₹50,000/month</td>
                <td>730+</td>
                <td>Valid passport, international travel history preferred</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>Super-Premium</strong></td>
                <td>₹1,50,000/month</td>
                <td>750+</td>
                <td>Existing bank relationship, invitation-only for some</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>Secured Cards</strong></td>
                <td>No minimum</td>
                <td>No minimum</td>
                <td>Fixed deposit of ₹15,000-₹5,00,000 with issuing bank</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>

          <h2>Documents Required</h2>
          <ul class="feature-list">
            <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Identity Proof:</strong> PAN Card (mandatory), Aadhaar Card, Voter ID, or Passport</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Address Proof:</strong> Aadhaar, utility bills (not older than 3 months), passport, or rent agreement</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Income Proof (Salaried):</strong> Latest 3-month salary slips, Form 16, and 6-month bank statement</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Income Proof (Self-Employed):</strong> Last 2 years' ITR, profit & loss statement, and 12-month bank statement</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Employment Proof:</strong> Company ID card, appointment letter, or employment certificate</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Passport-Size Photo:</strong> Recent photograph (some banks require this for physical verification)</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>How to Check Credit Card Eligibility</h3>
